OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1773288217
OL,3,CHome Secretary grants police request
OL,4,Cto ban Al Quds Day march
OL,6,FA pro-Palestinian march has been
OL,7,Fbanned from taking place on Sunday
OL,8,Fafter the home secretary approved a
OL,9,Frequest by the Metropolitan Police "to
OL,10,Fprevent serious public disorder".
OL,12,FThe annual Al Quds Day march, which
OL,13,Ftakes place in London, has drawn
OL,14,Fcriticism over its apparent backing
OL,15,Ffor the Iranian regime, after
OL,16,Forganisers expressed support for the
OL,17,Fcountry's late supreme leader
OL,18,FAyatollah Ali Khamenei, who was killed
OL,19,Fin US-Israeli strikes on February 28.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
