FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1773288217
OL,3,CHome Secretary grants police request
OL,4,Cto ban Al Quds Day march
OL,6,FSeveral counter-protests had also been
OL,7,Fplanned for the day.
OL,9,FAnnouncing her decision to ban the
OL,10,Fmarch, the home secretary said she was
OL,11,F"satisfied doing so is necessary to
OL,12,Fprevent serious public disorder, due
OL,13,Fto the scale of the protest and
OL,14,Fmultiple counter-protests, in the
OL,15,Fcontext of the ongoing conflict in the
OL,16,FMiddle East".
OL,18,FMs Mahmood added that, "Should a
OL,19,Fstationary demonstration proceed, the
OL,20,Fpolice will be able to apply strict
OL,21,Fconditions.
OL,26,@sD@AOUxD@LO]zD@XOU
