PN,31805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1773288217
OL,3,CHome Secretary grants police request
OL,4,Cto ban Al Quds Day march
OL,6,FThe Met said that previous Al Quds Day
OL,7,Fmarches have resulted in arrests for
OL,8,Fsupporting terrorist organisations and
OL,9,Fantisemitic hate crimes.
OL,11,FIn a statement, the Metropolitan
OL,12,Fpolice said: "The decision to ban it
OL,13,Fthis year is purely based on a risk
OL,14,Fassessment of this specific protest
OL,15,Fand counter-protests ` we do not
OL,16,Fpolice taste or decency or prefer one
OL,17,Fpolitical view over another, but we
OL,18,Fwill do everything we can to reduce
OL,19,Fviolence and disorder."
OL,26,@tD@NOU{D@WO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
